The paper discusses a representation of partial confidence in belief and preference that is consistent with decision theory, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses how this approach can be used during knowledge acquisition, which is relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and cybersecurity (cs.CY). Finally, the paper discusses the benefits and costs of additional modeling, which is relevant to systems and control (cs.SY).
